    <h2>1. Information Collection</h2>
    <p>We may collect personal information such as your name, email address, and other contact information when you register or use the services on our platform. This information is collected to improve user experience and for communication purposes only. By using our platform, you acknowledge that we may collect and store the data you provide.</p>

    <h2>2. Use of Information</h2>
    <p>We use the collected information to:
        <ul>
            <li>Provide and improve our services</li>
            <li>Respond to inquiries and feedback</li>
            <li>Send updates or promotional material (if you opt-in)</li>
        </ul>
    </p>
    <p>However, the content provided on MindCare, including any recommendations or analysis related to mental health or medical conditions, is for informational purposes only and <strong>should not be relied upon for diagnosis, treatment, or decision-making.</strong></p>

    <h2>3. Data Security</h2>
    <p>We take reasonable measures to protect the personal data you provide. However, please be aware that no method of internet transmission is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee the absolute security of your data.</p>

    <h2>4. Third-Party Services</h2>
    <p>MindCare may contain links to external websites or third-party services. We are not responsible for the privacy practices or the content of these external sites. Please review the privacy policies of these third-party services before providing any personal information.</p>

    <h2>5. Accuracy of Information</h2>
    <p>While we strive to offer accurate and helpful information, MindCare cannot guarantee the accuracy, reliability, or trustworthiness of the content. Any advice, suggestions, or content provided on this platform is not to be treated as professional medical or psychological counsel.</p>

    <h2>6. Disclaimer</h2>
    <p>By using MindCare, you understand and agree that the platform's content is <strong>not to be trusted</strong> as a reliable source of medical or mental health information. MindCare does not provide professional medical diagnoses, therapy, or treatment. Always consult a qualified healthcare provider for any concerns regarding your mental or physical health.</p>

    <h2>7. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
    <p>We reserve the right to update this privacy policy at any time. Any changes will be posted on this page, and you are encouraged to review this policy periodically.</p>

